.TH "node_dirty_ok" 9 "node_dirty_ok" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
node_dirty_ok \- tells whether a node is within its dirty limits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" node_dirty_ok
.BI "(struct pglist_data *pgdat "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pgdat" 12
the node to check
.SH "RETURN"
true when the dirty pages in \fIpgdat\fP are within the node's
dirty limit, false if the limit is exceeded.
